    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-12-06T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-12-06T07:00:00-05:00" n="918"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d918">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">775.00/12–650: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Merrell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Addis Ababa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-12-06T15:00:00+03:00"
                            >December 6, 1950—3 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>122. Emperor declared national holiday yesterday to celebrate <gloss
                        target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> decision on Eritrea. Populace genuinely happy
                    about decision. Emperor gave huge luncheon “on occasion of <gloss
                        target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> decision to restore Eritrea to Ethiopia”, during
                    which steady stream of women (Eritrean, according to Prime Minister at whose
                    table I sat) approached Majesties and kissed their feet.</p>
                <p>When I congratulated Emperor’s private secretary and said what a fine thing
                    decision was, he replied, “yes, and it is all due to you”, naturally meaning my
                    country.</p>
                <p>When I congratulated Emperor, he requested with obvious emotion that I convey his
                    deepest thanks to my government for all its assistance. Acting Minister Foreign
                    Affairs and Minister of Commerce also expressed their warmest appreciation and
                    made it clear that in their opinion credit for solution was mainly due US.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Merrell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
